# 🧠 Playwright AI Agent: Technical Deep Dive

This document provides a detailed, code-level explanation of the Playwright AI framework. It transitions from high-level concepts into the actual mechanics of the codebase, demonstrating how the deterministic system manages test execution, state, and concurrency.

---

## 1. System Initialization (`globalSetup.js`)

Before Playwright runs a single test, it executes `globalSetup.js`. This is where the framework bootstraps the "brain" of the agent—the `.agent/` directory.

```javascript
// globalSetup.js
module.exports = async function globalSetup() {
  fs.mkdirSync(AGENT_DIR, { recursive: true });
  
  const registryPath = path.join(AGENT_DIR, 'registry.json');
  // ... creates method_index.json, pending_patches.json
  
  if (!fs.existsSync(registryPath)) {
    fs.writeFileSync(registryPath, JSON.stringify(REGISTRY_DEFAULT, null, 2), 'utf8');
  }
};
```
**Key Takeaway:** The `registry.json` file begins as a completely empty shell (`{ "selectors": {} }`). The system relies entirely on **dynamic auto-registration** at runtime.

---

## 2. The Strict 4-Layer Execution Path

The framework enforces a hard segregation between locators, actions, business logic, and test assertions.

### Layer 1: Elements 
Returns raw Playwright locator builder functions. No actions are performed here.
```javascript
// src/elements/Login.elements.js
module.exports = {
  LoginElements: {
    usernameInput: (page) => page.locator('[data-test="username"]'),
    loginButton: (page) => page.locator('[data-test="login-button"]')
  }
}
```

### Layer 2: BasePage (ActionEngine)
This is the core interceptor. We never call `locator.fill()` directly. We pass the locator function to `BasePage.fill()`, which wraps the Playwright action in a `try/catch` to record health telemetry.
```javascript
// src/pages/BasePage.js
  async fill(registryKey, locatorFn, value) {
    try {
      await locatorFn(this.page).fill(value);
      this._recordSuccess(registryKey, locatorFn); // Log success to memory
    } catch (err) {
      if (_isLocatorError(err)) {
        this._recordFailure(registryKey, locatorFn); // Log failure to memory
      }
      throw err; // Re-throw to fail the test natively
    }
  }
```

### Layer 3 & 4: Page Objects and Specs
Page objects combine BasePage actions. Specs execute them.
```javascript
// src/pages/Login.page.js
async login(username, password) {
  // Notice the registryKey 'Login.usernameInput' mapping to the element
  await this.fill('Login.usernameInput', LoginElements.usernameInput, username);
  await this.click('Login.loginButton', LoginElements.loginButton);
}
```

