## 3. The Self-Healing Registry Internals

### A. Dynamic Introspection
When `BasePage` sees a `registryKey` it hasn't encountered before, it auto-registers it. It does this by directly parsing the Layer 1 javascript function as a string to extract the selector:

```javascript
// BasePage.js
function _extractLocatorInfo(locatorFn) {
  const fnStr = locatorFn.toString(); // e.g. "(page) => page.locator('#btn')"
  const match = fnStr.match(/=>\s*(.+)$/s);
  const locator = match ? match[1].trim() : null;

  let tier = null;
  if (/getByRole|getByLabel/.test(locator)) tier = 1; // Semantic
  else if (/data-test/.test(locator)) tier = 2;       // Hook
  else tier = 3;                                      // Structural
  
  return { locator, tier };
}
```

### B. Intelligent Error Classification
Not all failures mean a locator is broken. If a test fails because the internet disconnected, we don't want to rate the `#submit-btn` selector as `BROKEN`.

```javascript
// BasePage.js
function _isLocatorError(err) {
  const msg = err.message || '';
  
  // Environment issues - do NOT penalize the selector score
  if (msg.includes('Target closed') || msg.includes('net::ERR_')) return false;

  // Test Assertion logic failures (e.g. text was 'Hello' but expected 'World')
  // We use `expect(received)` as an exclusive Playwright assertion keyword
  if (msg.includes('expect(received)')) return false;

  // Pure locator failures - DOES penalize the selector score
  if (err.name === 'TimeoutError') return true; 
  if (msg.includes('detached from the DOM')) return true;

  return true;
}
```

### C. Concurrency Safety (`mergeAndSave`)
Playwright spawns multiple async Node.js worker processes to run tests in parallel. If Worker A and Worker B try to write to `.agent/registry.json` at the same time, one overwrites the other.

To fix this, `registry-manager.js` uses an atomic Lockfile Protocol:

```javascript
// registry-manager.js
mergeAndSave() {
  const lockPath = this.registryPath + '.lock';
  
  try {
    // 1. Spin-wait to acquire exclusive fs lock
    this._acquireLock(lockPath); 

    // 2. Read what other workers wrote to the disk while we were busy
    let diskData = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(this.registryPath, 'utf8'));

    // 3. Merge in-memory data with the disk data
    for (const key of allKeys) {
        // If both workers wrote the same key, pick the one with more test runs
        merged.selectors[key] = this._pickWinner(diskRec, memRec); 
    }

    // 4. Safely write back to disk atomically
    fs.writeFileSync(tmpPath, JSON.stringify(merged, null, 2));
    fs.renameSync(tmpPath, this.registryPath);

  } finally {
    // 5. Release lock for next worker
    this._releaseLock(lockPath);
  }
}
```

